Hubei Reshuai: the Great Test of anti-epidemic

By Zhou Qunfeng, staff writer

PUBLISHED: February 24,2020

Hubei is the main battlefield in the fight against the new crown disease. On February 13th, the party secretaries of Hubei Province and Wuhan City both got new faces.

On the same day, Hubei Province held a meeting of leading cadres, Vice Minister of the Organization Department of the Communist Party of China Central Committee Wu Yuliang attended the meeting, and announced the Central Decision: Comrade Ying Yong appointed Hubei Provincial Committee member, Standing Committee, Secretary; Wang Zhonglin is a member of the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee, a member of the Standing Committee and Secretary of the CPC Wuhan Municipal Committee.

Before that, Jiang Chaoliang was party secretary of Hubei Province and Ma was party secretary of Wuhan. For this personnel adjustment, people use an image to describe it as "walking horse for Jiang" .

Before taking office in Hubei, Ying Yong served as deputy secretary of the Shanghai Municipal Party Committee and Mayor; Wang Zhonglin served as member of the Standing Committee of the Shandong Provincial Party Committee and Secretary of the Jinan Municipal Party Committee. On the same day, it was unusual for a province and its provincial capital to make changes to its top party official.

Wu Yuliang said that the adjustment was based on the overall situation, the needs of the epidemic prevention and control work and the actual situation of the Hubei provincial leadership, through thorough consideration and careful study of the decision.

With Ying Yong's arrival in Hubei Province, Hubei officially entered the "Yingyong time" .

On his first day, he held three meetings in a row. To participate in the provincial leading cadres meeting, the afternoon he chaired a special meeting to study the next stage of prevention and control measures. He then addressed a meeting of leading cadres in Wuhan and stressed that he "hopes that everyone will take concrete actions to support Wang's work" .

After assuming his duties, "The prevention and control of the epidemic is a big test, it is a big battle, and the winner is the brave one who meets in the narrow road, " Ying Yong said on several public occasions. "The position of provincial Party secretary is a heavy responsibility and a heavy burden. It is also a big test for me. "

At present, Hubei epidemic situation is still unusually severe, complex and changeable. For Ying Yong and his new partners, their big test is just beginning.

A group of police officers prepares to enter Wuchang's shelter hospital on Feb. 11,2010, as they affix a police logo to their protective clothing. Photo / Hubei Daily, Wei re

"Heroic" to Hubei

Ying Yong was born in November 1957 in Xianju, Zhejiang Province. According to public information, he served as deputy director of the police station, mayor of the town, director of the Public Security Department of the Taizhou Administration, Director of the Public Security Bureau of Shaoxing, Deputy Secretary and Deputy Director of the Party Committee of the Public Security Department of Zhejiang Province, Deputy Secretary of the Disciplinary Committee of Zhejiang Province, director of the provincial supervision department, etc. , served as president of the High Court of Zhejiang Province, became a provincial and ministerial-level cadres. A year later, he moved to Shanghai and became secretary of the Leading party group and President of the Shanghai Higher People's Court. Since April 2013, he has been a member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Shanghai Municipal Committee, Minister of Organization, and later Deputy Secretary of the CPC Shanghai Municipal Committee. He served as executive vice mayor of Shanghai in September 2016 and as Mayor of Shanghai in January 2017.

In recent years, after the two sessions, Shanghai Mayor Ying Yong met with Chinese and foreign journalists to answer questions from the media. Ying Yong has a good memory and is familiar with a series of figures, the Global Times quoted a foreign journalist as saying.

On the night of January 20, Shanghai confirmed the first confirmed case of imported COVID-19 pneumonia.

After the new pneumonia spread to Shanghai, Ying Yong became head of the COVID-19's leading group for the prevention and control of the pneumonia epidemic. On February 1st he chaired a panel of experts, arguing that only a government that is open to scrutiny is a government that is tireless, and only a government that is open to criticism is a government that is progressive.

Ying Yong, who had grown up from the grass roots in Shanghai, paid special attention to the work of the grass roots in fighting the epidemic. He held many face-to-face meetings with medical experts and grass-roots representatives to listen to their opinions and suggestions on the prevention and control of epidemic situations. He said that the importance of grass-roots work should be emphasized, the burden of grass-roots work should be effectively reduced, and difficulties should be mostly solved for the grass-roots.

At a symposium, he said, "let's get straight to the point and talk about what problems, difficulties and good experiences and suggestions have been encountered in carrying out epidemic prevention and control work at the grassroots level. "

On February 11, Ying Yong hosted a symposium at the Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention to study the key issues of new pneumonia and the role of big data in accurate prevention and control.

Two days later, he left Shanghai for Hubei.

Ying Yong said that from the moment he set foot on the land of Jingchu, he became a member of Hubei Province, and the people of Hubei Province breathed together and shared the same fate. "together with all the cadres and people in the province, I will work with one heart and one mind to win the war of prevention and control of the epidemic, and live up to the trust and expectation of the Party and the people. "

Some analysts believe that, from the television screen, in Shanghai to fight the epidemic, Ying Yong most of the time wearing ordinary surgical masks, only when entering the Shanghai Municipal Public Health Clinical Center, will wear a medical protective mask. When he takes over as party secretary of Hubei Province, he will certainly have a better chance of showing up wearing a surgical mask.

Born in August 1962 in Fei County, Shandong Province, and five years younger than Ying Yong, Wang Zhonglin, who took office in Hubei Province on the same day as Ying Yong, graduated in Criminal Law from the East China University of Political Science and Law.

After graduating from university, he went to work for the Public Security Bureau in Zaozhuang. Like Ying Yong, he was also a cadre who came from the grass roots and had long experience in politics and law. He started as an ordinary clerk and worked his way up to become a member of the Party Committee of the Zaozhuang Public Security Bureau and a commander of the traffic police detachment. Later, he served as deputy chief procurator of the Zaozhuang People's Procuratorate and a member of the party group. He was also a member of the Standing Committee of the Zaozhuang Municipal Committee and the mayor of Liaocheng City, shandong Province Development and Reform Commission director, Jinan Mayor and other posts. In 2018, he was a member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Shandong Provincial Committee and Secretary of the CPC Jinan Municipal Committee.

Since January 24, the eve of the Lunar New Year, Wang Zhonglin has been working hard to prevent and control new pneumonia in communities, stations, factories and other areas, according to public reports.

Several political and business people in Jinan told China News weekly that Wang was very dedicated and gave the impression in Jinan that he was straightforward and cheerful, with a strong style and strong execution. When he investigates, he often adopts the method of "four-straight" , that is, no notice, no call, no report, no need to accompany the reception, and go straight to the grass-roots level, straight to the scene.

A senior media source said that Wang sometimes criticizes people, even severely, but he just doesn't take things personally. If afterwards he feels that the criticism has caused too much psychological pressure on others, even if the other party is just a member of the staff, he will call or explain to the client face to face, to let the other people off the psychological burden.

According to public reports, when directing the fight against the epidemic in Jinan, Wang Zhonglin used the "four unrequited loves" method, seven times to the city entrance and exit, stations, enterprises, communities, hospitals, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, agricultural markets, retail pharmacies, centralized quarantine points and other nearly 30 key areas of on-site supervision, coordination and problem-solving.

On Feb. 11, Wang Zhonglin's last public appearance in Jinan, he wore a mask and went to the neighborhood, pharmacy and Observation Center to supervise the epidemic prevention and control.

Two days later, he appeared in Hubei as Party Secretary of Wuhan. This is also his first inter-provincial exchange of posts.

On the day that Ying Yong assumed his new post, he held a special meeting and said six "key points" in a row: We should highlight key points, grasp the main contradictions and major aspects of the current prevention and control work, and make up in time for the shortcomings and weak links; we should spare no effort to do a good job of blocking, the key to stopping the spread of the epidemic is to control the source of the epidemic; to bring the Forces of prevention and control down on the communities, to fully implement the moderately closed management of the communities, to strengthen territorial responsibility, to strengthen the prevention and control of the communities, and to strengthen the prevention and control of the groups, watch your own people, mind your own business, and do your own O. we need to do a good job in treating them, intensify epidemiological investigations, and make thorough and thorough investigations, seek out the patients with latent infection, the close contacts of the confirmed cases, the suspected patients and the confirmed patients, do not leave a single family or a single person, and do everything possible to separate, collect and treat them, and constantly improve the diagnosis and treatment plan, we must ensure the supply of medical supplies, fully activate production capacity with strong policies, and support a number of leading enterprises, key enterprises and a number of small and medium-sized enterprises in expanding production capacity and switching to production and insurance, to further improve the supply capacity of medical products in Hubei Province.

The above six "key points" cover the treatment, barrier, material support and other three aspects of anti-epidemic content. This is also considered to be the main direction of Hubei in the future.

In the afternoon of the same day, at a meeting of leading cadres in Wuhan, Ying Yong commented on the new Wuhan Party secretary, Wang Zhonglin: he has good political quality, strong organizational and leadership skills, experienced at the grassroots level, is familiar with economic work and urban management, and works decisively, be Responsible, diligent and practical, and decent.

On their first day in Hubei Province, Ying Yong and Wang faced a grim set of figures: 4,823 new cases of pneumonia (including 3,095 clinically diagnosed cases) were reported in the province between 00 and 2400 on February 13, there were 116 new deaths (including 8 clinically diagnosed cases) . A total of 51986 cases (including 15384 clinically diagnosed cases) , 7593 severe cases and 1685 critical cases were reported in Hubei Province.

"Hubei and Wuhan are the decisive places to win the battle for epidemic prevention and control, and we must Gunbuster, " Ying said.

TREATMENT: strive to achieve "bed and other people"

After the outbreak of the epidemic, Hubei in the treatment of great pressure, disorderly medical treatment, bed tension and other issues prominent.

Yang Yunyan, vice governor of Wuhan, said on January 22 that a new pattern of centralized treatment of fever patients had been adopted to deal with possible cross-infection and spread of diseases caused by the current disorder of fever patients seeking medical treatment.

The pattern is also known as the "7 + 7" pattern, that is, in the vicinity of seven large hospitals such as Tongji Hospital and Zhongnan Hospital in the urban area, Wuhan has selected seven second-class public hospitals such as Hankou City Hospital and seven city hospitals as designated hospitals for fever outpatient clinics, transfer of patients, vacated ward all used to receive fever patients. In other words, Wuhan has set up seven designated hospitals, dedicated to the treatment of fever patients.

Since January 23, all patients with fever above 37.3 C in Wuhan have come to these 7 designated hospitals for treatment. At the same time, 7 large-scale hospitals have been arranged to help these 7 designated hospitals, which will take over other patients besides the patients with fever.

Ma Jing, head nurse of the intensive care isolation ward at central South Hospital, told China News weekly on Jan. 25 that the beds were still very tight under the above model, with three or four people coming in after each critical patient.

Since then, the central admission of patients with COVID-19 Pneumonia Vulcan Mountain Hospital, Raytheon Mountain Hospital, as well as admission of patients with mild cases of the Shelter Hospital has been put into use.

Zhang Yanling, former director of Beijing Xiaotangshan "SARS" hospital, directed the construction of Huoshenshan Hospital and Leishenshan Hospital in Wuhan. He told China News weekly that the two hospitals in Wuhan, which were built as a matter of urgency, played an important role. These two hospitals are superior to Xiaotangshan Hospital in scale, quality and scientific rationality of design.

However, due to the severe situation of the epidemic, the problem of the shortage of beds has not yet been fundamentally solved.

On February 14, Wang Zhonglin presided over the city of new pneumonia epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters Video Conference. He stressed that the current epidemic prevention and control situation in Wuhan is still very serious. To continue to build a new shelter hospital, the O increase beds, fully equipped with medical personnel and medical supplies, scientific optimization of the treatment process, improve the aid Han medical team services, and strive to increase the rate of admission and cure, to achieve the "bed and other people. ".

On February 15, Wang Zhonglin went into the hospital, the community, the supermarket and so on to investigate, and visited the sympathy front-line medical workers. "every second we move forward, we bring hope to more people, " Wang told a video conference at Wuhan's new CAP headquarters on the same day, stressing the need for quick implementation and strong execution in the epidemic prevention and control work

He also said that to strive for 3 days time, combined with big data means, home patients carpet-type, dragnet-type screening, figure out the bottom, to achieve "bottom. ".

Wang Zhonglin asked leading cadres at all levels to put themselves in their shoes, to treat patients as their brothers and sisters, as their parents and relatives, to clear the channels for seeking help, and to pay attention to the connection rate and handling rate, we must let the masses of the "hotline" to get through, can be effective.

On the morning of February 15, Ying Yong went to Jinyintan hospital in Wuhan, Square Hospital in Wuhan Living Room, Huoshenshan Hospital, Tongji Hospital, sino-french eco-city Hospital area, to understand the situation of patients admitted, and to visit the first-line medical staff. This is his first investigation since he took over as party secretary of Hubei Province.

During the investigation, he learned that many medical staff long-term overload work, told the hospital responsible person: "medical staff is our precious human resources, to do everything possible to protect our physical and mental health. "

On the morning of the same day, the Guoxin Administration held a press conference in Wuhan. As of 2400 hours on Feb. 14,217 medical teams and 25,633 medical team members had been dispatched from all over the country, not including those sent by the military, said Wang Hesheng, a member of the party group and Deputy Director of the National Health Commission and a member of the Standing Committee of the Hubei Provincial Party Committee. Three Mobile P3 laboratories were mobilized, with 181 medical teams and 20,374 medical staff in Wuhan, 36 medical teams and 5,259 medical staff in other cities. This is well above the scale and speed of the 2008 Sichuan Earthquake's 2008 mobilization. The central government has also arranged for 19 provinces to adopt the "one province, one city" approach to support Hubei Province.

Wang also revealed that nine shelter hospitals have been opened, with more than 6,960 beds and 5,606 patients. As a next step, part of the hospital wards will continue to be vacated as necessary, part of the venue will be requisitioned and converted into a designated hospital and a shelter hospital to ensure that patients and suspected patients who have been identified and diagnosed can be admitted centrally, make sure the number of all patients not admitted to the hospital is zero.

According to Jiao Yahui, deputy director of the Medical Administration and Hospital Authority of the National Health Commission, the discharge rate of patients from the first two designated hospitals in Wuhan, namely the Jinyintan Hospital and the Wuhan Lung Hospital, has reached 30% to 39% . "that number gives us a lot of confidence. "

Jiao Yahui also said that the shelter hospital is currently admitted to the diagnosis of mild cases of patients, diagnosed with mild cases admitted to the Shelter Hospital, will not lead to the risk of cross-infection.

On February 16, the Hubei Provincial Party Committee and the provincial government issued an opinion calling on all localities to speed up nucleic acid testing so that both the confirmed patient admission and the suspected patient's nucleic acid testing could be cleared on the same day.

On the same day, Ying Yong presided over a meeting of commanders of the provincial defense and Control Headquarters to adjust the composition of the provincial defense and Control Headquarters and the division of responsibilities, there are 5 working groups under the provincial control and Prevention Headquarters, including the office and the Comprehensive Group, the medical treatment and disease control group, the material and market guarantee group, the propaganda group and the Social Stability Group.

Before this Hubei Province prevention and control headquarters, sets down the working group to include the social donation group, the material safeguard group, the transportation safeguard group and so on.

On the day he took office as Party secretary of Hubei Province, Ying Yong said that it was necessary to ensure the supply of medical materials, fully activate production capacity with a strong policy, support a number of leading enterprises, key enterprises and a number of small and medium-sized enterprises to expand production capacity, shift production to guarantee supply, further improve the supply capacity of medical and nursing products in our province.

Block: More than 80 minutes issued three blocking orders

Treatment and isolation are the two key links in the fight against the epidemic. The former is "treatment" and the latter is "prevention" .

The community is the most basic and basic unit of epidemic prevention and control. Only by defending the community can the whole society have a more solid foundation of prevention and control. He said that to do everything possible to stop the spread of the epidemic, control of the source is the key. To prevent and control the sinking of the community, the full implementation of moderately closed community management, strengthen territorial responsibility, strengthen community prevention and control, strengthen group prevention and control, look after their own people, manage their own doors, do their own thing.

Recently, many cities in Hubei Community Management and control measures upgrade.

On February 13, a meeting of the central leading group to deal with the epidemic of NCP made it clear that Xiaogan, Huanggang and other places should adopt the same measures of isolation and treatment as Wuhan. Hubei and Wuhan should further strengthen the management and control of the passage from Han to Hubei, and effectively achieve internal non-proliferation and external anti-export.

On the same day, Huanggang New Crown Pneumonia Epidemic Prevention and control headquarters issued an emergency notice: from today, in the city-wide upgrade control measures, all small areas (residential areas) are fully closed management. In addition, Dawu County, Xiaogan City, and other places are also fully closed management.

Recently, many places in Hubei also implemented "wartime control. ".

On February 13, the COVID-19 pneumonia control headquarters in Yunmeng County, Xiaogan City, issued an emergency announcement to impose wartime control in the city of Yunmeng. The circular made it clear that all residents who forcibly break into isolated, cordoned off or sealed off facilities in residential areas, courtyards, buildings and road entrances and exits shall be detained in accordance with the relevant provisions of wartime management.

It is worth noting that these two days Hubei Province has carried out a series of epidemic prevention and control measures. At present, Shiyan Zhangwan District, Dawu County, Xiaogan City, Yunmeng County, and other places have announced the implementation of wartime control.

According to official announcements in the above-mentioned regions, wartime control was urgently implemented on the basis of relevant laws and regulations, such as the law on penalties for public security management, the law on the prevention and control of infectious diseases and the regulations on emergency response to public health emergencies.

But Mao Shoulong, a professor at the Institute of Public Finance and Public Policy at Renmin University of China's School of Public Administration and Executive Vice President of the institute, told China News weekly that the concept of "wartime" Is Not a very precise word. "It's the military language of public administration, but it's not the language of the law, " Mao Shoulong said, "It means that in the event of an outbreak, the government has the power to take control measures. "

Heavy snow falls in Wuhan on February 15. In the afternoon, Ying went to three communities in Wuhan to check on the prevention and control of the epidemic and to visit community workers and volunteers.

Ying Yong acknowledged the practice of registering people in and out of the Waterfront Star City community, where they must check their body temperature. He paid tribute to and thanked the grassroots community workers and volunteers, and also asked the staff to convey greetings to residents through the wechat group. In the Huangli road community, he detailed understanding of government officials sinking community, grid search and so on. Hejiadun community, China Eastern Airlines community to implement strict management, while opening the purchase of vegetables, takeout, express delivery temporary storage, residents need to be delivered by the staff of the community, since February 2, no new cases.

"Hubei Daily" reported that Ying Yong encouraged officials and community workers from the sunken community in their exchanges that day, "To fully understand the feelings of the masses, to stand up to grievances, to stand up to complaints, and to guide the masses to 'stay at home' is to be responsible not only to oneself, but also to others and to society. "

After the investigation, Ying Yong presided over the provincial Standing Committee (expanded) meeting overnight, to promote the deployment of the province's epidemic prevention and control work. At the meeting, it was proposed to strengthen classified management, to implement full-scale screening and screening, and to implement management measures for the "four categories of people" (people with latent infection, people in close contact with the confirmed cases, suspected patients and confirmed patients) , we should make every effort to strengthen community management and control, and implement the most strict 24-hour management measures.

Some community cadres have also felt the strength of the recent sinking of government officials.

Tianmendun community, Tangjiadun Street, Jianghan district, Wuhan, is less than 2 km away from the South China seafood market and originally had 26 community workers. Under the epidemic, 2 people resigned, leaving only 24 people on the post, managing more than 30 residential areas, 8,135 residents, including many old residential areas, community workers generally reflected heavy workload.

On February 16, Zheng Qingxia, secretary of the Party branch of Tianmendun community, told China News weekly that in recent days, cadres from the relevant organs at the municipal and district levels had sunk into her community, these cadres came from the Wuhan Tax Bureau, the Yangtze daily and other units. "In two days, 32 people have reported. In addition, there are more than 40 staff members arranged by the Urban Management Bureau and the traffic bureau, who are also gradually entering the streets. Most of these cadres are staff members. When they come to the community, they will follow the community's arrangements, stand on duty, do propaganda work and help the community make all kinds of phone calls."

"100% of the village community closed 24-hour Management" , is Wang Zhonglin recently grasp a key point. How do you achieve your goals? He stressed the need to firmly strengthen source control.

"It is useless to shout empty slogans and engage in formalism, " Wang said, reminding cadres at all levels that "every day the epidemic drags on, the cost is huge" and that "the prevention and control of the epidemic is not good and other development, reform and stability are empty talk. "

At a press conference held by the Guoxin Office in Wuhan, Hubei Province on the morning of February 15, Wang Hesheng, deputy director of the National Health Commission and a member of the Standing Committee of the Hubei Provincial Committee, said that the epidemic prevention and control has reached the most critical stage, and that Wuhan, Hubei Province is still the main battlefield, work has now sunk into the community to make sure there is no second Wuhan.

On Feb. 16, at 15:46,16:57, and 17:12, three heavy notices were issued about the closed management measures of urban and rural communities and village groups, according to Government of the People's Republic of China:

The circular of the People's Government of Hubei Province on further strengthening the prevention and control of NCP requires that all village groups, communities, subdivisions and settlements in urban and rural areas should be under the strictest 24-hour closed management All residents of the dynamic rolling screen network, so that "do not leave a door, do not fall a person, constantly one day, " to ensure full coverage, no blind area. In case of violation of the level I response control measures for major public health emergencies or obstruction of the prevention and control of the epidemic situation, the Public Security Bureau shall take compulsory measures according to law.

The notice on strengthening the closed management of urban communities and residential areas requires that all residential areas, buildings and doorways, under the premise of ensuring fire safety, in principle only one entrance and exit are reserved, and residents are not allowed to go out without special circumstances, each household sends out one person every three days to buy daily necessities.

The notice on strengthening the closed management of rural groups requires that the natural village group (Village Bay) be used as a unit for hard isolation, and in principle each village group (Village Bay) retain an entrance and an exit, and arrange for personnel to reinforce duty. Non-members of the village group (Village Bay) and vehicles are not allowed to enter, and each household can send one person every three days to purchase essential daily necessities and urgently needed agricultural Means of production. In case of violation of the Provisions on the management of first-level emergency response to major public health emergencies, the judiciary shall take measures according to law.

On the same day, Ying Yong also chaired a video dispatch meeting on epidemic prevention and control and stressed that the epidemic should be resolutely prevented from spreading from urban to rural areas. Hubei and Wuhan should be aware of the overall situation of epidemic prevention and control in the responsibility and weight. Compared with other provinces and cities in the country. "The situation in our province, city and prefecture is very serious. In addition to Wuhan, there are five regions where thousands of cases have been confirmed. "

Hubei Province new crown pneumonia epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters issued a circular, requiring all types of enterprises in the province not earlier than February 20 before 24:00 to resume work. In addition, colleges and universities in Hubei Province, primary and secondary schools, secondary vocational schools, technical colleges, kindergartens postponed the start of school. The specific opening time will be determined after scientific assessment and announced to the public in advance according to the situation of epidemic prevention and control.

"The epidemic is like a mirror, reflecting the different state of the cadres. "

In the fight against the epidemic at the same time, Hubei officialdom how to solve the old disease, also became Ying Yong and others in front of a test.

Ying Yong affirmed the previous phase of Hubei's epidemic prevention work. "In the previous stage, the vast majority of Party members and cadres in Hubei, especially in Wuhan, did a lot of hard work and made great efforts, " he said

From the implementation effect, whether it is taken before the decision-making of the closure of Wuhan, or the construction of Fire Mountain Hospital, Raytheon Mountain Hospital, Shelter Hospital, etc. , have achieved positive significance. But the performance of several local officials has also been controversial.

Wuhan Mayor Zhou Xianwang, wearing a mask, gives an interview to CCTV on Jan. 27. He said, "In this case, we have both an under-disclosure side and an under-disclosure side that we use a lot of good information to improve our work. Infectious Diseases have an infectious disease prevention law, which must be disclosed in accordance with the law. As a local government, I can not disclose it until I am authorized to do so."

An expert from the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences told China Newsweek that Zhou's claim that he, as mayor of Wuhan, could not disclose the epidemic to the public without authorization was indeed based on the law of the People's Republic of China on the Prevention and control of infectious diseases. However, the law of the People's Republic of China on emergency response, adopted at the twenty-nine th meeting of the Tenth Standing Committee of the National People's Congress on August 30,2007, has stipulated the relevant "early warning" mechanism, and give the local government full autonomy.

"If the Wuhan municipal government finds such cases, it should be aware of the risk of public health incidents and immediately initiate public health alert according to the law instead of waiting for authorization, which is certainly not the case, " the experts said.

Article forty-three of the Emergency Response Law of the People's Republic of China stipulates that when the possibility of an impending or impending occurrence of a natural disaster, accident disaster or public health event that can be forewarned increases, local Government of the People's Republic of China at or above the county level shall, in accordance with the relevant laws, administrative regulations and the limits of authority and procedures prescribed by the State Council, issue an alarm at the corresponding level, and decide and announce that the area concerned shall enter an early warning period, at the same time report to the Government of the People's Republic of China, if necessary, report to the higher level, and to the local garrison and may be endangered by the adjacent or related areas of Government of the People's Republic of China.

The expert said that previously, if the Wuhan municipal government applied the law flexibly, it could have given early warning before reporting it, and informed the people in time about how to protect themselves against the virus. According to the law, even if there is a deviation from the warning, will not be held accountable. "The Wuhan municipal government is legally required to give early warning of this outbreak, but it is wrong not to. "

According to the expert, the Wuhan government should announce an alert period as early as around December 29,2019, in accordance with the Emergency Response Law of the People's Republic of China.

The reason for this conclusion, he is based on December 29, Hubei Province Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital began to the provincial, municipal, district CDC report; Hubei Province and Wuhan Health Commission instructed Wuhan Center for Disease Control, Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital and Kong Hon District Center for Disease Control to Hubei Province Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital to start epidemiological investigation. It can be concluded that the Wuhan municipal government should have reached the conclusion that "the public health event is about to happen or the probability increases" around this time point.

Before this, Hubei still has a number of officials to express publicly"guiltily, blame oneself".

Ma Guoqiang, then secretary of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee, said during an appearance on CCTV that, "This is a time of guilt, guilt, self-reproach. I have been thinking that if I had made a decision earlier and taken the kind of drastic control measures that we are taking now, the results would have been better, the impact on the whole country would have been smaller, and the Party Central Committee and the State Council would have been less worried."

At a news conference in Hubei Province at 21pm on January 30, Jiang Chaoliang, the Party secretary at the time, bowed in apology, said he felt a heavy heart and offered his deep condolences to his compatriots who lost their lives in the epidemic. "In this epidemic prevention and control work, we did take some measures in some places, although the starting point is good, but the working method and method are a little simple, I apologize to everyone. "

Jiang Chaoliang also said he would "reflect deeply on the shortcomings in the local governance system and governance capacity test, and earnestly learn lessons" .

Officials in Hubei Province have been blamed for the outbreak.

On January 30, Tang Zhihong, director of Huanggang's Health Commission, was removed from his post. Earlier, the Central Steering Group sent an inspection team to Huanggang to conduct inspection and verification. When asked about the number of hospital admission capacity beds, nucleic acid testing capacity and other issues, Tang Zhihong and others were accused of asking three do not know.

On February 4, the Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision of Hubei Province made a public announcement on the dereliction of duty by the leaders and cadres of the Hubei Red Cross Society. According to the circular, Zhang Qin was removed from his post as a member of the Hubei Red Cross party group and a full-time vice-president, and was given a serious warning and a major demerit in administrative records Serious inner-party warnings and major demerit punishments shall be given to Chen Bo, member of the Party Group of the Red Cross Society of Hubei Province, and inner-party warnings shall be given to Gao Qin, secretary of the party group and executive vice-president of the Red Cross Society of Hubei Province. Other persons in charge of the Red Cross Society of Hubei Province shall be handled by the Party organizations concerned in accordance with the rules and regulations in accordance with their cadres'administrative authority.

According to the circular, after investigation, the leaders and cadres of the Red Cross Society of Hubei Province did not take responsibility for receiving and distributing donations during the epidemic prevention and control period.

Two days before his dismissal, Zhang Qin said in an interview with China News weekly that there had been mistakes in the work of the Hubei Red Cross and that more work would be required in the future.

On Feb. 10, the Hubei Provincial Standing Committee decided to remove Zhang Jin from his position as party secretary of the Provincial Health Commission and Liu Yingzi from his position as director of the Provincial Health Commission, both of which were filled by the newly appointed Provincial Standing Committee member, Wang Hecheng.

On February 14, Wang Zhonglin presided over a regular video conference of the new crown pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters in Wuhan. It is worth noting that Wang Zhonglin also brought to Wuhan the experience of "Four incompatibilities" when he was in charge in Jinan.

He said that strict supervision and inspection, to take the "four is not two straight" approach, serious investigation and punishment do not take as a problem. We should care about the front-line workers, arrange the rest rotation reasonably, make every effort to ensure other treatment for medical and epidemic prevention personnel, and pay attention to the inspection and identification of cadres in the front-line of epidemic prevention and control.

There are many signs that the composition of official circles in Hubei will be further optimized in the fight against the epidemic.

On February 15th Ying Yong presided over a meeting of the provincial Party Committee's (enlarged) Standing Committee, at which he offered a vivid metaphor: an epidemic is like a mirror, a ruler, which reflects the different state of the cadres and measures their achievements. We should not only make strict demands on cadres, but also take care of them, so as to make the two hands of supervision, accountability and encouragement and care hard and solid. We should inspect cadres on the front line of Epidemic Prevention and control, and strive to hand in a qualified answer sheet in the big test of epidemic prevention and control.

The next day, he hosted a video conference on the disease control and Prevention and stressed that we must resolutely put an end to formalism and bureaucracy, and that it is only right to fight and win wars. "We should inspect cadres in the line of fire, praise and reward outstanding performance, bold use, dereliction of duty, perfunctory serious accountability. ".

Among the officials who entered Hubei this time, in addition to Wang Hesheng, who has a professional background in health care, ying Yong, Wang Zhonglin and Chen Yixin, the secretary general of the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission, who arrived in Wuhan on Feb. 8, when Chen Yixin took over as deputy head of the Central Guidance Group, all have long histories of working in the political, legal, and political systems.

Zhou Enlai, a professor at the Nankai University, has management experience in the mega city of Shanghai. Wang Zhonglin has served as the head of several prefectures in Shandong Province and has rich experience in grassroots governance, this will help the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee and the CPC Wuhan Municipal Committee strengthen the management and coordination of prevention and control work at all levels and optimize the decision-making and handling of specific problems in their future work; Wang Hesheng is an expert official in the health system, there are National Health Commission work experience, is for Hubei Province epidemic prevention and control into more "professional" force.

Dai Yanjun, deputy director of the Department of Party building, teaching and research at the Central Party School (National School of Administration) , said in an interview with China News weekly that the most important point of the personnel adjustment in Hubei is that the adjusted officials have no ideological burden, the new leaders must have new ideas. Their arrival will arouse people's expectations, dispel their doubts and lift their spirits. From the performance of the previous work, shows that Hubei, Wuhan's leadership team, in the fight against the epidemic in the capacity needs to be strengthened. Therefore, the central government should proceed from reality and transfer more advantageous cadres to shoulder leading responsibilities in the past, which is meaningful for strengthening the commanding force and leading force in the front line of Epidemic Prevention.

Dai said the use of key people in key positions was an important factor in determining whether expected accomplishments could be achieved. Secretary of the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee and Secretary of the CPC Wuhan Municipal Committee are key posts. Many of the officials after this adjustment have rich experience in political and legal work. Their arrival will help inject more "rule of law forces" into the anti-epidemic work. It's also based on reality. Because at the present special moment, we should mobilize all kinds of social forces and take some unconventional measures to solve the problem.

"their background in the rule of law allows them to carry out the spirit of central leadership and create an external environment conducive to the prevention and control of the epidemic in their specific work. They can also handle various issues in strict accordance with the law and ensure that the epidemic prevention work is carried out in an orderly manner, " Dai said.
